INTRODUCTION
In today’s rapidly evolving digital world, digital literacy has become an essential skill for students across all disciplines, including engineering. It not only involves the ability to use digital tools effectively but also includes understanding how to communicate professionally, collaborate online, and stay safe from cyber threats.
This project was designed to provide hands-on experience with various digital platforms and tools that are commonly used in academic and professional environments. It also aimed to build awareness regarding responsible online behavior and cybersecurity practices.
Through this project, I explored tools such as GitHub, LinkedIn, HackerRank, and Google Forms. Additionally, I learned the importance of structured communication through professional emails and gained insights into cybercrime and its prevention. This project has significantly contributed to improving my technical, communication, and digital awareness skills.
TASK 1: DIGITAL LITERACY INFOGRAPHIC
In this task, I designed a Digital Literacy Infographic using Canva, a widely used online design platform that allows users to create visually appealing content with ease. The main objective of this task was to present key concepts of digital literacy in a clear, concise, and engaging format that can be easily understood by students.
The infographic included important components such as the definition of digital literacy, commonly used digital tools, safe internet practices, professional online behavior, and email etiquette. I specifically highlighted tools like Google Docs, GitHub, and LinkedIn, which are essential for academic work, collaboration, and career development. Additionally, I incorporated guidelines for safe internet usage, such as using strong passwords, avoiding suspicious links, and protecting personal information.
One of the main challenges I faced was organizing a large amount of information into a single-page design without making it cluttered. To overcome this, I carefully structured the layout using headings, icons, and color schemes to enhance readability and visual appeal.
This task helped me improve my skills in visual communication, content organization, and creative thinking. It also gave me a deeper understanding of digital literacy and its importance in both academic and professional environments.

TASK 2: DIGITAL PORTFOLIO
The objective of this task was to create and maintain a professional digital portfolio using platforms such as GitHub and LinkedIn. These platforms play a crucial role in building a student’s professional identity and showcasing their skills, projects, and achievements to a wider audience.
I created and updated my GitHub profile by organizing repositories and uploading relevant project files. GitHub is an essential tool for version control and collaboration, widely used in the software and engineering industries. It allows users to track changes, manage projects efficiently, and demonstrate their technical abilities through practical work.
In addition, I created a LinkedIn profile to establish my professional presence online. I added important details such as my academic background, field of study, and career interests. LinkedIn is a valuable platform for networking, connecting with professionals, and exploring internship and job opportunities.
This task helped me understand the importance of maintaining a strong digital presence in today’s competitive environment. It also encouraged me to think about my future career goals and how I can present myself professionally.
In the future, I plan to regularly update my profiles with new projects, certifications, and achievements, which will help me build a strong portfolio and improve my career prospects.

TASK 3: CODING & COLLABORATION PLATFORMS
In this task, I explored coding and collaboration platforms that are widely used by students and professionals in the field of engineering and technology. I created an account on HackerRank and solved a beginner-level programming problem. This helped me understand the basics of coding logic, problem-solving techniques, and the importance of practice in improving programming skills.
HackerRank is a popular platform that provides coding challenges in various programming languages. It is widely used for skill development and technical interview preparation. By solving problems on this platform, I was able to enhance my logical thinking and gain confidence in my coding abilities.
In addition to coding, I also created a Digital Literacy Quiz using Google Forms. The quiz included multiple-choice and short-answer questions related to digital tools, communication, and online safety. I linked the form to Google Sheets, which allowed automatic collection and organization of responses. This feature is particularly useful for analyzing data and tracking participation.
This task demonstrated how digital tools can be effectively used for learning, assessment, and collaboration. It also improved my ability to use online platforms for academic purposes and manage digital content efficiently.

TASK 4: EMAIL ETIQUETTE & SOCIAL MEDIA AWARENESS
This task focused on developing professional communication skills and understanding responsible behavior on social media platforms. As a student and future professional, it is important to communicate clearly and respectfully in digital environments.
In this task, I drafted two professional emails. The first email was written to a professor requesting an extension for an assignment submission. The second email was addressed to an internship coordinator expressing interest in a summer internship opportunity. While writing these emails, I ensured that they followed proper email etiquette, including a clear subject line, formal greeting, structured body, and appropriate closing.
Additionally, I created a checklist of social media do’s and don’ts. This included guidelines such as maintaining a professional profile, using respectful language, verifying information before sharing, and avoiding the posting of inappropriate or offensive content. These practices are essential for maintaining a positive digital presence.
Through this task, I understood that poor digital communication can lead to misunderstandings and negative impressions. For example, sending an unstructured or informal email to a professor may result in delayed responses or miscommunication.
Overall, this task helped me develop strong communication skills and understand the importance of professionalism in both academic and online environments.

TASK 5: CYBERCRIME AWARENESS
In this task, I studied cybercrime with a focus on phishing, which is one of the most common types of online fraud. Phishing involves attackers impersonating trusted entities such as banks, institutions, or companies to trick individuals into revealing sensitive information such as passwords, banking details, or OTPs.
A typical phishing attack begins with a fake email or message that appears legitimate. The message often creates a sense of urgency, asking the user to verify their account or update their information by clicking on a link. This link redirects the user to a fake website that closely resembles the original. When the user enters their details, the attacker captures the information and uses it for fraudulent activities.
Students are often targeted in such attacks because they frequently use digital platforms but may not always be aware of these threats. The consequences of phishing include financial loss, identity theft, and unauthorized access to personal accounts.
To prevent such attacks, it is important to avoid clicking on suspicious links, verify the authenticity of messages, use strong passwords, and enable two-factor authentication. Users should also never share sensitive information like OTPs.
This task increased my awareness of cyber threats and encouraged me to adopt safer online practices.

CONCLUSION
This Digital Literacy Project has been highly beneficial in enhancing my understanding of digital tools, professional communication, and cybersecurity awareness. It provided practical exposure to platforms that are essential for academic and professional growth.
Through this project, I developed important skills such as problem-solving, digital communication, and online collaboration. I also became more aware of cyber threats and the importance of safe online practices.
Overall, this project has prepared me to effectively use digital technologies in my academic journey and future career, making me a more responsible and informed digital user.

